The given triple appears to be incorrect because a city, Indianapolis, cannot be the head of government. A city is a location, not a person or an entity that holds a government position. Therefore, the triple "Indianapolis headOfGovernment William H. Hudnut III" is grammatically inconsistent and likely contains an error.\n\nA corrected version would involve stating that William H. Hudnut III is the head of government for a specific country, state, or region, not for a city. For example:\n\n"William H. Hudnut III is the head of government of [Country/State/Region]."\n\nHowever, without additional context or clarification, the original triple remains inconsistent.
